	dprr:hasNoteText "Dedicated the first temple of Mercury, being elected by the people for this purpose while primipilus to express their dislike of the Consuls (Liv. 2.27.6; Val. Max. 9.3.6). Münzer suggests that he may have been a Decemvir sacris faciundis (APF 89f.; cf. Wissowa 304)." .
